(Kamiya) We will make it public when the full-scale launch occurs.

236
00:13:51,531 --> 00:13:55,969
This will also lead to increasing the brand value of our hospital.

237
00:13:56,036 --> 00:13:58,471
That's all from me.

238
00:13:58,538 --> 00:14:02,909
Dr. Mitsui will be in charge of the mother and child emergency department.

239
00:14:02,976 --> 00:14:04,911
I will leave the selection to you.

240
00:14:04,978 --> 00:14:06,980
(Mitsui) Yes.

241
00:14:12,485 --> 00:14:13,987
(Mitsui) Ah.

242
00:14:17,991 --> 00:14:19,492
(Mitsui) Whoa.

243
00:14:21,494 --> 00:14:23,496
(Nagasaka) Huh? (Mitsui) Hmm.

244
00:14:24,998 --> 00:14:27,934
(Nagasaka) So why me?

245
00:14:28,001 --> 00:14:29,936
(Mitsui) You helped me yesterday.

246
00:14:30,003 --> 00:14:31,938
You're a good guy~

247
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:34,441
>> He might be someone I don't care about.

248
00:14:34,507 --> 00:14:36,443
(Nagasaka) Yes? (Mitsui) And still →

249
00:14:36,509 --> 00:14:38,445
It's not dyed any color.

250
00:14:38,511 --> 00:14:42,449
I think I'll dye it my own color~ Hehehe...｡

251
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:44,451
(Nagasaka) “Fufufu”. (Kurata) A little bit like that→

252
00:14:44,517 --> 00:14:46,953
It violates power harassment and sexual harassment.

253
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:48,955
(Nagasaka) Anyway, there are other newcomers besides me, right?

254
00:14:49,022 --> 00:14:51,958
(Mitsui) I understand, because I understand.

255
00:14:52,025 --> 00:14:54,961
Next time, the skin will be crispy and the meat will be juicy →

256
00:14:55,028 --> 00:14:57,464
Treat yourself to Kagawa Prefecture's famous chicken with bones and beer.

257
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:59,466
(Nagasaka) You can't get caught with something like that.

258
00:14:59,532 --> 00:15:01,968
(Mitsui) Hmm, then ah!

259
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:06,406
At the famous hormone shop "Mori Mori Butchigiri" in Shin-Okubo →

260
00:15:06,473 --> 00:15:08,908
Added a large serving of Marucho and a glass of lemon sour!

261
00:15:08,975 --> 00:15:10,910
(Nagasaka) Why does it all involve drinking?

262
00:15:10,977 --> 00:15:14,414
(Mitsui) It's small, but it's a sure happiness that won't let you down.

263
00:15:14,481 --> 00:15:17,417
(Nagasaka) Huh? (Mitsui) The scene of childbirth is a series of betrayals.

264
00:15:17,484 --> 00:15:22,422
But I will never disappoint when it comes to delicious food and alcohol.

265
00:15:22,489 --> 00:15:24,924
That's what you mean. (Nagasaka) What do you mean?

266
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:28,428
(Kurata) Mr. Nagasaka: Are you prone to getting caught up in things? (Nagasaka) Huh?

267
00:15:28,495 --> 00:15:30,931
(Narimiya) I agree with you on that point.

268
00:15:30,997 --> 00:15:33,433
Have you had similar experiences in the past?

269
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:36,936
(Nagasaka) Come to think of it... What kind of constitution is this?

270
00:15:37,003 --> 00:15:38,938
>> It's impromptu, but what do you think?

271
00:15:39,005 --> 00:15:40,940
(Mitsui) Wow, great!

272
00:15:41,007 --> 00:15:42,942
>> As expected, this is professional work.

273
00:15:43,009 --> 00:15:45,945
At the request of the director, I will also be responsible for my regular duties.

274
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:47,447
(Mitsui) Thank you.

275
00:15:47,514 --> 00:15:51,451
>> Narumiya-san, I have a qualification as a social worker, which is helpful!

276
00:15:51,518 --> 00:15:53,953
It's only natural that Mr. Kurata will be participating.

277
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:58,024
Yeah, if it's for Mr. Mitsui...

278
00:15:59,526 --> 00:16:04,397
Oh, and we also need the cooperation of neonatologists and anesthesiologists.

279
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:08,401
Now then, which story and who? →

280
00:16:08,468 --> 00:16:11,471
Should I blackmail you?

281
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:17,911
(Narimiya) How to deal with pregnant women who have many uncertainties.

282
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:20,914
As an anesthesiologist, you want someone who is a professional in obstetric anesthesia.

283
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,483
(Mitsui) There is someone I have an unrequited love for.

284
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:32,425
(Mitsui) Ah, “Doctor Justice” I’m a fan too.

285
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:35,929
It was so powerful that you posted it the other day.

286
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:39,432
You exposed the cover-up of medical errors at a major hospital.

287
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:42,435
(Todo) What is it for? (Mitsui) No, it's extremely real.

288
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:45,438
That was definitely drawn by a medical professional.

289
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:48,942
>> What is it for? (Mitsui) Denounces the darkness in the medical world.

290
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:50,944
Kya~ I wonder what kind of person he is.

291
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:54,948
Well, I guess she's an honest and honest woman like me.

292
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:58,451
I said it myself hahaha...

293
00:16:58,518 --> 00:17:01,454
>> Warm up the place →

294
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:04,391
I refuse because you're trying to start something unpleasant.

295
00:17:04,457 --> 00:17:06,893
(Mitsui) No, just listen to me.

296
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,896
>> I'm listening to what the director is saying.

297
00:17:09,963 --> 00:17:11,398
I'm a freelancer.

298
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:13,400
That's why that director's dark rumors →

299
00:17:13,466 --> 00:17:15,402
I hear it from other people as well.

300
00:17:15,468 --> 00:17:18,405
There's definitely something wrong this time too. (Mitsui) Huh.

301
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:20,974
(Todo) You're not interested in me in the slightest.

302
00:17:22,976 --> 00:17:24,911
(Mitsui) Anyway, once the team is complete →

303
00:17:24,978 --> 00:17:27,981
You can save lost lives.

304
00:17:29,983 --> 00:17:33,987
Mr. Todo's arm type.

305
00:17:35,989 --> 00:17:38,925
>> I don't think we're both in the same mood.

306
00:17:38,992 --> 00:17:42,429
Since I am a freelancer, I choose the risks I take on myself.

307
00:17:42,495 --> 00:17:46,933
Being a doctor is a profession, not a charity.

308
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,436
(Monitor) Leaving behind a baby boy who just gave birth →

309
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:52,439
He is suspected of abandoning it.

310
00:17:52,505 --> 00:17:54,941
(Monitor) In response to the police investigation, the girl →

311
00:17:55,008 --> 00:17:57,944
"I gave birth and gave up my baby," she said.

312
00:17:58,011 --> 00:18:01,948
(Mitsui) A spilled life.

313
00:18:02,015 --> 00:18:05,385
What happens when you don't give up?

314
00:18:05,452 --> 00:18:07,387
Don't you want to know?

315
00:18:07,454 --> 00:18:10,390
>> Ah...

316
00:18:10,457 --> 00:18:12,892
I'll make a prediction.

317
00:18:12,959 --> 00:18:17,964
You're going to be the subject of "Doctor Justice" someday.

318
00:18:25,972 --> 00:18:28,408
(Monitor) “I couldn’t talk to anyone →

319
00:18:28,475 --> 00:18:30,910
I had no choice but to do this.''

320
00:18:30,977 --> 00:18:33,980
The circumstances that led to the abandonment of the baby...

321
00:18:44,491 --> 00:18:46,926
(Nagasaka) [Sorry, I'm in a hurry]

322
00:18:46,993 --> 00:18:56,936
♪～

323
00:18:57,003 --> 00:18:59,439
(Narumiya) I see. (Nagasaka) I see.

324
00:18:59,506 --> 00:19:00,940
>>Join the team→

325
00:19:01,007 --> 00:19:04,878
It's not just a tendency to get involved.

326
00:19:04,944 --> 00:19:08,381
There is no such thing as a person without a past.

327
00:19:08,448 --> 00:19:10,884
(Nagasaka) That's scary though.

328
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:12,886
Who is Narimiya-san?

329
00:19:12,952 --> 00:19:14,954
>> I'm just a concierge.

330
00:19:26,466 --> 00:19:27,901
(knock)

331
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:29,903
(Kamiya) Please.

332
00:19:29,969 --> 00:19:32,906
(Kaori) Sorry to bother you. (Kamiya) What's wrong with you two?

333
00:19:32,972 --> 00:19:34,908
>> Celebration Mother's favorite apple pie.

334
00:19:34,974 --> 00:19:36,409
(Kamiya) Ah...｡

335
00:19:36,476 --> 00:19:39,412
>> Your mother is going to become a grandmother.

336
00:19:39,479 --> 00:19:42,916
(Kamiya) Huh? (Kaori) I'm pregnant.

337
00:19:42,982 --> 00:19:46,920
(Kamiya) Ah, congratulations!

338
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:49,923
>> Thank you. (Kamiya) Yeah!

339
00:19:49,989 --> 00:19:52,425
Congratulations to Mr. Tominaga as well.

340
00:19:52,492 --> 00:19:54,928
>>We don't know what will happen during childbirth.

341
00:19:54,994 --> 00:19:57,430
I can't be happy until the baby is born safely.

342
00:19:57,497 --> 00:20:00,433
Dad is extremely straight-laced.

343
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,435
Please don't look like me.

344
00:20:02,502 --> 00:20:04,938
It's troubling to have a rough resemblance to you.

345
00:20:05,004 --> 00:20:07,440
That's terrible, Papa. (Kamiya) Ahahaha...｡

346
00:20:07,507 --> 00:20:09,008
📱(vibration sound)

347
00:20:12,011 --> 00:20:14,948
(Tominaga) Looks like it was found. (Kamiya) Huh?

348
00:20:15,014 --> 00:20:16,950
>> This is a pregnant woman who ran away from birth.

349
00:20:17,016 --> 00:20:21,454
(Mitsui) This is an NPO organization that my friend runs.

350
00:20:21,521 --> 00:20:24,457
It's like a go-to temple for pregnant women who are in trouble.

351
00:20:24,524 --> 00:20:27,460
(Nagasaka) Is this something that involves doctors?

352
00:20:27,527 --> 00:20:29,963
(Mitsui) You are also the mother of the baby who was present.

353
00:20:30,029 --> 00:20:31,965
(Nagasaka) So? (Mitsui) Leave it alone→

354
00:20:32,031 --> 00:20:33,967
Don't you feel anxious?

355
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:36,469
(Nagasaka) Moya? (Mitsui) If you remain in a haze →

356
00:20:36,536 --> 00:20:39,472
You won't be able to enjoy today's reward.

357
00:20:39,539 --> 00:20:41,474
(Nagasaka) That again.

358
00:20:41,541 --> 00:20:43,977
(Mitsui) Yonezawa beef corned beef topped with chopped new onions →

359
00:20:44,043 --> 00:20:46,980
I'm planning on playing a highball.

360
00:20:47,046 --> 00:20:48,982
(sound of window opening)

361
00:20:49,048 --> 00:20:51,050
I'm coming, Sanada-san.

362
00:20:55,054 --> 00:20:57,991
(Hatori) If I met you once... >> I don't want to meet you.

363
00:20:58,057 --> 00:21:00,493
If I have to pay for it, I'll pay it properly later.

364
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,429
That kid...

365
00:21:03,496 --> 00:21:06,432
Have someone else raise you.

366
00:21:06,499 --> 00:21:08,434
That's fine, right?

367
00:21:08,501 --> 00:21:10,436
(Nagasaka) Huh…｡

368
00:21:10,503 --> 00:21:12,438
(Asuka) What? Do you have anything to complain about?

369
00:21:12,505 --> 00:21:14,507
(Nagasaka) No, sorry.

370
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:18,945
(Mitsui) Why am I alone?

371
00:21:19,012 --> 00:21:20,446
>> Huh?

372
00:21:20,513 --> 00:21:25,018
(Mitsui) I wonder why my mother let me go.

373
00:21:28,521 --> 00:21:33,026
(Mitsui) If things continue like this, the baby will live with that feeling.

374
00:21:35,028 --> 00:21:37,964
Even if you decide to adopt a child, you have to meet them once...

375
00:21:38,031 --> 00:21:41,534
(Sound of tapping on desk) That's why! I don't want to see you.

376
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,975
(Sound of door closing) Well→

377
00:21:49,042 --> 00:21:51,978
I'll protect you at home for a while.

378
00:21:52,045 --> 00:21:54,480
I don't want to see you, I want to see you →

379
00:21:54,547 --> 00:21:56,983
I want to see you, but I don't want to see you.

380
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:58,985
(Nagasaka) Huh…｡

381
00:21:59,052 --> 00:22:01,988
>>Haha, how many times do you sigh?

382
00:22:02,055 --> 00:22:04,424
(Nagasaka) I've been here twice.

383
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:08,928
>> I've heard that he's a harmless newcomer, but there's something rebellious about him.

384
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:12,932
(Nagasaka) You're done, right? Let's go home, Mr. Mitsui.

385
00:22:12,999 --> 00:22:14,934
(Megumi) Ugh...｡

386
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:16,936
(Nagasaka) Mr. Mitsui?

387
00:22:17,003 --> 00:22:19,439
(Mitsui) When did that girl come?

388
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:22,942
(Hatori) Three days ago, you searched on the internet and contacted us.

389
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:24,944
(Nagasaka) You look incredibly happy.

390
00:22:25,011 --> 00:22:28,448
>>First of all, being connected is most important.

391
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:31,951
Neglected by his mother from an early age →

392
00:22:32,018 --> 00:22:34,954
It seems like he barely went to school.

393
00:22:35,021 --> 00:22:38,958
I left home a year ago to work part-time at a distribution center.

394
00:22:39,025 --> 00:22:41,461
To the boyfriend I met there→

395
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:43,963
When I told her about my pregnancy, she ran away →

396
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:46,966
I can't even go to work anymore.

397
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:52,472
I'm struggling with money and haven't been able to go to the hospital yet.

398
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:55,041
(Nagasaka) I haven't been diagnosed again.

399
00:22:57,543 --> 00:22:59,545
Mr. Mitsui?

400
00:23:05,985 --> 00:23:08,421
(Mitsui) 31 to 32 weeks.

401
00:23:08,488 --> 00:23:10,923
The symptoms of headache and lightheadedness occurred →

402
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:14,427
This is because gestational hypertension syndrome is quite advanced.

403
00:23:14,494 --> 00:23:15,928
Mr. Nagasaka.

404
00:23:15,995 --> 00:23:19,432
(Nagasaka) There is something called the placenta inside the uterus→

405
00:23:19,499 --> 00:23:21,434
If this isn't done well →

406
00:23:21,501 --> 00:23:24,937
The baby will not be getting enough nutrients and oxygen.

407
00:23:25,004 --> 00:23:28,441
It is said that blood pressure increases in an attempt to compensate for this.

408
00:23:28,508 --> 00:23:31,444
>>My blood pressure is close to 150→

409
00:23:31,511 --> 00:23:35,448
Visual disturbances and headaches are also common.

410
00:23:35,515 --> 00:23:37,517
(Mitsui) Please stay in the hospital.

411
00:23:40,019 --> 00:23:42,455
(Megumi) Impossible! I can't grow it.

412
00:23:42,522 --> 00:23:45,458
There are other ways to get support in your life.

413
00:23:45,525 --> 00:23:47,460
The government will also take action.

414
00:23:47,527 --> 00:23:50,963
(Megumi) If I have to give birth to someone else...

415
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:54,467
You can adopt a child, right?

416
00:23:54,534 --> 00:23:57,537
(Mitsui) I heard you talking at the facility.

417
00:24:00,039 --> 00:24:03,476
It was my life in my womb for 8 months.

418
00:24:05,478 --> 00:24:10,416
Mr. Shishido, please think again about what you want to do.

419
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:12,985
I won't leave you alone.

420
00:24:20,493 --> 00:24:30,436
(baby crying)

421
00:24:30,503 --> 00:24:45,017
♪～

422
00:24:50,523 --> 00:24:53,459
I've been waiting for you. Please.

423
00:24:53,526 --> 00:24:56,028
Thank you for your hard work.

424
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:02,468
(Nagasaka's voice) Trial operation canceled?

425
00:25:02,535 --> 00:25:05,404
(Kurata) I think that's what will happen at today's board meeting.

426
00:25:05,471 --> 00:25:07,907
Or will the director push through?

427
00:25:07,974 --> 00:25:10,409
And Mr. Kagawa at the reception →

428
00:25:10,476 --> 00:25:13,913
It seems like she broke up with her anesthesiologist, Dr. Tadokoro.

429
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:16,415
Is that what you're talking about on the same level? (Kurata) Yes.

430
00:25:16,482 --> 00:25:20,419
(Takagi) That's great. If it's canceled, would you like to go to dinner with me?

431
00:25:20,486 --> 00:25:21,921
(Nagasaka) Yeah...｡

432
00:25:21,988 --> 00:25:23,923
>> What? That lack of clarity.

433
00:25:23,990 --> 00:25:25,925
(Nagasaka) A little bit about Professor Mitsui.

434
00:25:25,992 --> 00:25:27,927
>> Get all your thoughts out.

435
00:25:27,994 --> 00:25:30,429
(Nagasaka) I don't feel like backing down even if it gets cancelled.

436
00:25:30,496 --> 00:25:32,431
What is that guy?

437
00:25:32,498 --> 00:25:34,433
If you really want to be close to a specific pregnant woman →

438
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:37,436
It's extremely mental, and it's a high-risk birth →

439
00:25:37,503 --> 00:25:39,438
It does not necessarily mean that they will be born safely.

440
00:25:39,505 --> 00:25:42,441
>> Yeah yeah So? (Nagasaka) But that person→

441
00:25:42,508 --> 00:25:45,945
What can I say, it looks fun.

442
00:25:46,012 --> 00:25:48,447
An oddball? weirdo?

443
00:25:48,514 --> 00:25:51,951
>> Mr. Mitsui is an oddball and an eccentric person.

444
00:25:52,018 --> 00:25:54,453
If the situation gets out of control, there will be more slander →

445
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,455
I've made the decision. (Nagasaka) Huh?

446
00:25:56,522 --> 00:25:58,457
Ah! (Mitsui) Because I was on the right side →

447
00:25:58,524 --> 00:26:00,960
I heard you perfectly. (Nagasaka) Sorry.

448
00:26:01,027 --> 00:26:03,462
Ah, I've been curious about it for a while now →

449
00:26:03,529 --> 00:26:05,398
That right?

450
00:26:05,464 --> 00:26:07,900
(Mitsui) Ah.

451
00:26:07,967 --> 00:26:10,403
Can't you hear me? (Nagasaka) What?

452
00:26:10,469 --> 00:26:12,405
(Mitsui) Congenital rubella syndrome.

453
00:26:12,471 --> 00:26:17,410
Well, it was because the person who gave birth to me didn't go to the hospital properly.

454
00:26:17,476 --> 00:26:21,414
However, the first cry of a baby is different.

455
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:23,916
Something →

456
00:26:23,983 --> 00:26:27,987
I feel like I can hear properly with both ears.

457
00:26:32,992 --> 00:26:34,927
(elevator arrival sound)

458
00:26:34,994 --> 00:27:02,021
♪～

459
00:27:14,467 --> 00:27:17,970
Why are you moving now?

460
00:27:21,474 --> 00:27:24,910
(Sound of cell phone falling) Uh...

461
00:27:24,977 --> 00:27:27,913
(Female) What happened? OK?

462
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:30,916
OK? Be strong.

463
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:32,985
Someone please help!

464
00:27:34,987 --> 00:27:37,923
Didn't the person who called for help find out about things?

465
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:40,926
A real celebrity is someone with a big heart.

466
00:27:40,993 --> 00:27:44,430
However, just to be safe, I had them sign a non-disclosure agreement.

467
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:46,499
Work is fast.

468
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:53,439
(Mitsui) Mr. Shishido: The baby's blood pressure has become quite high and the baby is not getting enough oxygen.

469
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:56,509
An emergency caesarean section is required immediately.

470
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:01,447
>> \Ichinose-san, are you okay? /

471
00:28:01,514 --> 00:28:02,948
(Tsukimura) Are you okay?

472
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:04,950
(Mitsui) Mr. Shishido in the operating room. (Sumimoto) Yes.

473
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:06,952
